Rating: 3
I made this for my sister's birthday. On the whole, it was a picturesque cake and a grand success. If you plan accordingly, the cake isn't too time consuming. I made the almond cream filling the day before, chilled it for more than 3 hours, returned to it to add the whipped cream and left it in the fridge for the rest of the night until ready to use the following day. I did not encounter any problems with the cream being too runny, and thus did not have any of my cake layers slide (as some other reviewers had happen to them). As long as you chill the pastry cream thoroughly, you will not have this problem. However my only criticism would be the lack of almond flavour being detected in any component of the cake... and this was after I had already made my own changes to the recipe. For the extracts, I increased all the amounts by 1/8 tsp. For the cake itself, I ground up 1/2 cup blanched almonds and incorporated that into the mixture. Even with these alterations, the almond flavour was still very faint. I used 3 9-inch round baking tins instead of the 2 10 -inch tins and it came out just as well-- but watch the baking time as it is shorter. Finally, as other reviewers mentioned, do not forget to reserve 3/4 cup of the almond cream filling for the frosting.

