Rating: 4
I made this cake twice... out of necessity. The first time I followed the directions exactly and it turned into a sliding mess. It tasted great but looked awful and was time consuming. At that point I was very short on time so I used several shortcuts that made it turn out nearly as good and in about 1/4 the time. For you die-hard-cook-from-scratchers out there, I realize my method will leave me open for ridicule, so please don't. I used a french vanilla boxed cake mix, added the almond extract and a splash of vanilla extract and baked. Then, used pre-made cream cheese frosting and also added almost extract to that. When the cakes cooled, I actualyl scooped out about 1/4" of the lower layer, leaving about 1/2 rim around it. Bear with me! Then, spooned in some raspberry preserves that I'd had sitting in a little warm water to make softer, added some boxed jello vanilla pudding (which I also added some almond extract to) and a thin layer of cool whip. When I put the other cake layer on top, it effectively sealed in the filling and I was able to frost with the cream cheese frosting and add my berries. Unconventional I know, but I made it to the party and everyone RAVED about my cake and asked how I did it. Hope this helps some of you bakers who are always short on time like me.!

