Rating: 4
I have just made this recipe for the 3rd time and I think it is fantastic. I made one change in technique which I think solves the problem of lumpy almond paste: process the almond paste with the flour and sugar in the food processor, until you have a sand-like consistency. I even blended the eggs into it right in the bowl of the food processor, then the vanilla bean cream. Adding the warm cream to the sugar-egg mixture is called "tempering" and should prevent the cooked-egg consistency of the filling

