This was a very impressive cake. I made it for a family reunion...it was the only dessert that disappeared within minutes. My uncle said that it was the best cake he'd ever eaten! The only changes that I made to the recipe were these: I used seedless black raspberry jam instead of red raspberry, I added Ranier and Bing cherries to the berries on top of the cake and I omitted the red currant jelly glaze. No, it is not a cheap or fast cake to make but I very rarely bake so I was able to justify the time and expense required to make this dessert.

