Expensive and time consuming--but I wouldn't hesitate to make it again! This cake was perfect for summer: light, refreshing and not too sweet. It wasn't hard to make either, just be sure to set aside plenty of time to make it. Before you start, though, be sure to read the instructions carefully. Example: you have to put in an uneven amount of batter in the cake pans and part of the filling must be set aside for incorporating into the frosting. But for all the work and time you put into it, you will be justly rewarded!

