Rating: 3
A perfect 4th of July cake or even a wedding cake! I wanted to avoid the "heavy cake" syndrome, especially after a big BBQ dinner last night. I cut back on the frosting, using a thin coat even though I had leftover frosting. I also used low-sugar preserves for the filling layers which kept the sweetness-per-bite down. I piped a "rope" around the top of the cake to keep the fruit in place rather than building up a thick outer frosting edge. Very good recipe!

