Rating: 3
This cake was very well received for a birthday bash. I used 2 9 inch diameter cake pans as these were the largest I had. I cut the cakes in 2 and had a wonderfully impressive 4 layer cake. The cake itself is light and delicious. I added some fresh berries between the layers and used a skewer in the center of the cake to anchor the 4 layers prior to frosting. I would not use the almond extract in the frosting next time and would substitue some additional citrus zest instead as I felt the extract overpowered the other flavors. I would definately make this again and probably will do so for a July 4th event.